quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  45,1,"Ha'. Mim."
  45,2,"This Book is a revelation from the Most Mighty, the Most Wise.",footnotes:181328:1
  45,3,"Behold, for those who believe there are (myriad) Signs in the heavens and the earth",footnotes:181329:1
  45,4,"and in your own creation; and in the animals which He spreads out over the earth too there are Signs for those endowed with sure faith;",footnotes:181330:1
  45,5,"and in the succession of night and day, and in the provision that Allah sends down from the sky wherewith He gives life to the earth after it had been lifeless, and in the change of the winds: (in all these) there are Signs for people who use reason.",footnotes:181331:1,footnotes:181332:2,footnotes:181333:3,footnotes:181334:4
  45,6,"These are Allah's Signs that We rehearse to you in Truth. In what kind of discourse after Allah and His Signs will they, then, believe?",footnotes:181335:1
  45,7,"Woe to every guilty impostor"
  45,8,"who hears Allah's Signs being rehearsed to him, and yet persists in his pride, as though he had not heard it. Announce to him, then, the tidings of a grievous chastisement.",footnotes:181336:1
  45,9,"Whenever he comes to know anything of Our Signs, he makes them an object of jest. For such there awaits a humiliating chastisement.",footnotes:181337:1
  45,10,"Hell is behind them. Their worldly earnings shall not avail them, nor those whom they took as protectors instead of Allah. An awesome chastisement lies in store for them.",footnotes:181338:1,footnotes:181339:2